cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new approach for compressive sensing (CS) image reconstruction using a convolutional neural network. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the importance of good measurements in CS image recovery, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed network involves simultaneous training of multiple components, which is a common technique in neural network optimization (cs.NE) sub-category.
